story.title: New Year's Switch - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: Alexis: I just got you an invite to one of the hottest New Year’s parties in town!
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Lauren Hawkeye is a NYT and USA Today bestselling author of contemporary and erotic romance.

messages.text: I just got you an invite to one of the hottest New Year’s parties in town!
Do you know me at all?
I hate New Year’s.
I’m not letting my baby sister spend New Year’s at home…
With nothing but a bottle of cheap wine to kiss at midnight.
I am not your baby sister.
Two minutes. I was born TWO MINUTES after you.
In England, those two minutes would mean the difference between the heir and the spare.
I love being called the spare 🙄
Bottom line is, you’re going to this party.
Emma, you know how this is gonna go.
You can argue all you want…
But in the end, you always give in.
Fine.
Fantastic! There’s just one thing I haven’t told you yet…
Here we go…
I need you to pretend to be me.
Oh, hell no.
Don’t you remember the Josh Green incident?
I’m not pretending to be you to go on a date…
Just because you don’t know how to say no.
Cut Josh some slack.
He’d just broken up with his girlfriend.
And he spent the entire night asking me how to get her back.
He made me call her and tell her I thought he was a great guy!
Okay, so maybe he was little…odd.
You think?
But this time is different.
Do tell 🙄
I’ll let you choose this time!
Choose what?
Which date you want!
I thought you said you were sending me to a party.
That’s the exciting part.
Two hot parties. Therefore, two hot guys.
I think Mom and Dad dropped you on your head as a child.
Oh, come on.
Who’s it going to hurt?
Uh, ME.
And the guy that thinks they’re on a date with YOU.
Will you at least hear me out?
Do I have a choice?
Okay, party number one is a masquerade ball at DaVinci’s.
That super-expensive new club downtown?
How did you talk your way into that?
Because your potential date is the son of the owner.
His name is Marco. He’s Italian. He’s gorgeous.
And obviously he’s super rich.
So why don’t YOU go to his party?
Because I’m selfless and I’m letting you choose.
Sigh.
K, party number two is a pool party.
In DECEMBER?
Obviously it’s an indoor pool. Focus, please.
It’s a house party.
But the house is one of those huge new ones in Newport Heights.
How do you know someone who lives in such a fancy neighborhood?
Oh ye of little faith. His name is Dylan—
And he owns some kind of tech internet company thing.
Well, that clears things right up.
Which one do you want?
Neither! I want neither!
Why not? They’re both great catches.
For YOU.
They have dates with YOU.
We have identical DNA. So you kind of are me. Technically speaking.
My eye is twitching.
Eat a banana. I hear that helps. Now choose.
I have plans.
With who?
Cabernet and Sauvignon.
I already told you that cheap wine does not count as a date.
Why do you always do this? You need new life rules.
Say yes to the dates you actually want to go on.
Say no to the ones you don’t.
I repeat, say no.
Do not say yes and assume that your long-suffering twin sister will pick up your slack.
That’s the problem. I want to go on both dates.
I like both guys. And I don’t want to give either one up.
I fail to see how this is my problem.
Please, Em? Just this one last time.
I’ll never ask you to pull a twin switch again.
Oh, really?
Well, until…next time?
Dude.
Have you thought about their feelings at all?
How would Marky Mark and Donnie feel if they knew it wasn’t actually you on the date?
Marco and Dylan. Pay attention, please.
And that’s the beauty of it. They won’t know.
You’re not going to go away until I agree, are you?
You know me so well.
Fine. But this is the absolute last time.
You are the best baby sister in the world.
You’re making my eye twitch again.
Which one do you want?
Don’t say neither.
Well, I’d rather stab myself in the eyeballs with toothpicks than go to a club on New Year’s Eve.
So I guess I’ll take the house party guy.
You won’t regret this.
I sincerely doubt that.
Open the door.
What?
I’m outside. Open the door.
Emma sighs and trudges over to the door to look through the peephole.
Her sister is on the other side.
She opens the door.
Hey, baby sister.
Shouldn’t you be sucking up to me right now instead of ticking me off?
Don’t be so sensitive.
Alexis holds out her phone.
I just texted Dylan.
Probably a good idea for you to take over, so you’re not walking into the date cold.
Heaven forbid.
Sarcasm doesn’t become you.
Au contraire, sister dear. I’m fluent in it.
Emma reluctantly takes her sister’s phone.
She examines the photo assigned to the contact.
The guy in the picture has messy dark brown hair, a charming five o’clock shadow…
And thick-rimmed glasses.
He looks serious.
But something playful dances behind his eyes.
And he’s actually pretty hot.
But…
Not your usual type.
Alexis shrugs and Emma begins to type.
I’m really looking forward to New Year’s.
Me, too. I can’t believe I found the perfect girl to kiss at midnight.
Emma winces.
She glances at her sister, smirking to herself as she types the next words.
I can’t believe that I met someone who shares my love of eighteenth-century literature.
And Firefly fanfiction.
And who is also a feminist!
What are the chances?
I know, right? We have so much in common!
Emma pauses, then frowns.
You…like eighteenth century literature?
I didn’t make that clear when I brought up Robinson Crusoe five minutes after meeting you?
And btw Emma, I’m totally holding you to that New Year’s Day Firefly marathon.
DID YOU JUST CALL ME EMMA?
Um…isn’t that your name?
Emma drops the phone and points at her sister.
WHAT is happening?
Twin switch. Duh.
Alexis laughs at her dumbfounded sister’s expression—
Then gathers her twin into a hug.
Within minutes of meeting this guy, I knew he was perfect for you.
You couldn’t have just given him my number?
I had to seize the moment! Reel him in!
He’s not a fish.
Okay, fine. It was just more fun this way.
You should have seen the look on your face.
If I’d been born first I would have shoved you back in.
Come on. Are you telling me you’re not even a little bit interested?
You don’t have ANY butterflies from the hot geek—
Who can recite Robinson Crusoe to you…
As you make out with Firefly playing in the background?
Emma feels her cheeks flush.
She looks down at the phone.
She can’t deny it — she wants to meet Dylan.
He sounds like the perfect guy for her.
You’ve got me.
I’ll go.
But, wait a second—
What were you gonna do if I chose the other guy? Marco?
There is no Marco.
Alexis smiles an impish grin.
Unbelievable.
Just thank me and move on, woman.
Fine…thanks.
Alexis smirks at her sister, then shrugs.
See? You should have listened to your big sister all along.
I should have?
But next time we do a twin switch—
Stop. Stop right there.
What?
I love you. And I appreciate this.
But?
No more twin switches!
